title: DIARY-Emerging Markets Economic Events to Oct 2
text:
Sept 21 (Reuters) -
For other diaries, please see:

Government debt auctions
Political and general news events
Index of all diaries
Guide to economic indicators
** This Diary is filed daily *** MONDAY, SEPTEMBER 21 ABUJA - Central Bank of Nigeria holds monetary policy meeting (to Sept. 22). PRETORIA - South African Reserve Bank starts its three-day monetary policy committee meeting (to Sept. 23). MEXICO CITY - Central Bank of Mexico publishes monetary policy statement - 1800 GMT. TUESDAY, SEPTEMBER 22 PARIS - Launch of OECD's International Migration Outlook 2015, containing analysis on recent developments in migration movements and policies in OECD countries. OECD Secretary-General Angel Gurria and OECD Director for Employment, Labour and Social Affairs Stefano Scarpetta will present the Outlook's findings at the OECD Conference Centre. MAKATI CITY - Asian Development Bank releases update to its 2015 Asian Development outlook - 0130 GMT. BUDAPEST - Central bank of Hungary holds rate-setting meeting. NAIROBI - Central bank of Kenya announces rate decision. ABUJA - Central bank of Nigeria announces rate decision - 1330 GMT. WEDNESDAY, SEPTEMBER 23 PRETORIA - South African Reserve Bank announces rate decision - 1300 GMT. THURSDAY, SEPTEMBER 24 MANILA - Central bank of Philippines holds monetary policy meeting to announce interest rates - 0800 GMT. TAIPEI - Central Bank of the Republic of China (Taiwan) announces rate decision - 0900 GMT. PRAGUE - Czech National Bank holds monetary policy meeting to announce interest rates - 1100 GMT. JERUSALEM - Bank of Israel announces rate decision - 1300 GMT. SATURDAY, SEPTEMBER 26 CHISINAU - National bank of Moldova holds monetary policy meeting. An interest rate decision is expected. TUESDAY, SEPTEMBER 29 TOKYO - OECD E-Leaders 2015 (to Sept. 30). OECD Deputy Secretary General Mari Kiviniemi will deliver opening remarks. MUMBAI, India - Reserve Bank of India holds monetary policy meeting to announce interest rates. WEDNESDAY, SEPTEMBER 30 WASHINGTON - International Monetary Fund Managing Director Christine Lagarde participates in conversation hosted by the Council of Americas on global economic policies and prospects - 1430 GMT. BUCHAREST - Central bank of Romania holds board meeting, to announce interest rates - 0700 GMT. BANGKOK - Central Bank of Thailand releases its economic forecast - 0030 GMT. BANGKOK - Central Bank of Thailand will publish the minutes of September policy meeting - 0200 GMT.
FRIDAY, OCTOBER 2 PRAGUE - Czech National bank will publish the minutes of September governing board meeting - 0700 GMT.
